50|$|The Arabian oryx (Arabic: المها العربي) is the {{national}} animal of Jordan. The Arabian oryx is a medium-sized antelope with a distinct shoulder hump, long <b>straight</b> <b>horns,</b> and a tufted tail. It is a bovid, and the smallest member of oryx genus, native to desert and steppe areas of the Arabian peninsula.|$|R
